# Prestige Rewards Backend

Read `docs/CONTEXT.md` for full project context before non-trivial changes.

## Stack
- Medusa 2, TypeScript, PostgreSQL, WSL2 (run all commands from Ubuntu, not PowerShell)
- Path: `~/prestige-rewards-backend`

## Conventions
- Admin = Medusa `user` actor. Agent/Employee = Medusa `customer` actor with row in `agent`/`employee` table via `customer_id`.
- Categories = Medusa `ProductCategory` linked to `Company` via module link (`src/links/product-category-company.ts`). No custom category tables.
- After link changes: `npx medusa db:migrate`
- Tests: `npm run test:unit` (files in `src/__tests__/`)

## Do not touch without explicit request
- GoldieOrder model / redeem workflow / Stripe (teammate's branch)
- README unless syncing docs

## Code style
- Match existing route/workflow patterns
- Minimal diffs, no over-engineering
